main event: An unidentified flying object was tracked on radar over the central Pacific Ocean on 9 April 1963.
interesting points: The object was heading eastbound and was initially reported as a possible satellite., The object was sighted by a Navy aircraft at coordinates 32° 32N 177° 20W., The radar tracked the object for approximately 45 minutes., It reached an altitude of 42,000 ft., The object was reported to be the size of a pin.
